fields.description: Use AWS SDK for writing tests based on S3 API. Execute the tests against S3 and Walrus for uncovering compatibility issues.
fields.summary: Check API compatibility with AWS Java SDK

comments.body:
What we need to do here is exercise the AWS Java SDK against Walrus and check coverage and which calls we are failing (except for the features that we don't obviously have).

Here is the Javadoc for AmazonS3Client: http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSJavaSDK/latest/javadoc/com/amazonaws/services/s3/AmazonS3Client.html

Here is a start - 

https://github.com/wwannemacher/aws-compatibility-tests

I will keep adding to it as I work on other issues.
since you took this over and have been writing tests for eutester4j
[~swathi], is the test suite complete at this point?

[~tjcramer], I wouldn't say its complete as that involves exercising every permutation and combination of the several options that S3 API provides. I might have decent coverage for the bucket and object APIs that are used most often. I'm still working on it and adding new tests to the suite every day. Are you asking because the ticket is marked for 3.4? If so, I would prefer keeping the ticket open for another release or two as its an ongoing effort and cannot be addressed entirely in 3.4.

This is a placeholder for APIs that have been tested so far
